onal calculus and anomalous diffusion are closely connected with heavy tail limit theorems. Heavy tails are applied in finance, insurance, physics, geophysics, cell biology, ecology, medicine, and computer engineering. The goal of this book is to prepare graduate students in probability for research in the area of fractional calculus, anomalous diffusion, and heavy tails. Many interesting problems in this area remain open. This book will guide the motivated reader to understand the essential background needed to read and unerstand current research papers, and to gain the insights and techniques needed to begin making their own contributions to this rapidly growing field.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 4aAnomale Diffusion. 4aGebrochene Analysis. 4aGrenzwertsatz. 7aMATHEMATICS / Probability & Statistics / Stochastic Processes.2bisacsh1 aSikorskii, Alla, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut0 cEPUBz97831105591490 cprintz978311055907140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311055914940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110559149423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110559149/original  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK